manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: MSI: For Gamers & Creators MSI is one of the most trusted names in gaming and esports with countless hours and significant resources invested into premier esports leagues and tier-1 gaming teams. By supporting and working with the best of the best, MSI is able to integrate competitive gaming knowledge and aspirations with technological innovation to create new products that shatter today's performance limits. MAG B760 TOMAHAWK WIFI DDR4 Unite as One The MAG B760 TOMAHAWK WIFI DDR4 is a gaming-oriented ATX motherboard constructed around the latest Intel B760 chipset that balances value with premium hardware. Supports Intel Core 12th & 13th Gen Processors (LGA 1700) 12 Duet Rail Power System with 75A DrMOS 4 x DDR4 DIMMs with Memory Boost: Dual Channel (128GB Max. / 5333MHz OC) 1 x PCIe 5.0 x16, 1 x PCIe 3.0 x16 slot Lightning Gen4 M.2 & Shield Frozr 7.1 HD Audio with Audio Boost Realtek 2.5G LAN, Intel Wi-Fi 6E & Bluetooth 5.3

B760 Chipset, 12 Duet Rail Power System, Smart Cooling, DDR4 Memory Boost Supports Intel Core 12th & 13th Gen Processors The MAG B760 TOMAHAWK WIFI DDR4 motherboard supports 12th & 13th Gen Intel Core, Pentium Gold, and Celeron processors. Form Factor: ATX Socket Type: LGA 1700 Chipset: Intel B760 12+1 Duet Rail Power System with 75A DrMOS With its dual 8 pin power connectors and exclusive Core Boost technology, the MAG B760 TOMAHAWK WIFI DDR4 is able to sustain heavy CPU power loads to support system-demanding game settings: Digital PWM IC12-Phase Duet Rail CPU Power (DrMOS / 75A)1-Phase GT Power1-Phase AUX Power Integrated Cooling Features VRM Cooling: Features an extended heatsink, 7W/mK thermal pads and additional choke thermal pads for improved thermal dissipation. PCB Cooling: Premium 6-layer server-grade printed circuit design with 2 oz. thickened copper improves heat dissipation & reliability. SSD Cooling: M.2 Shield Frozr prevents thermal throttling. System Cooling: Connect and synchronize cooling with strategically placed pin-headers - including a dedicated pump-fan header. 4 x DDR4 Dual Channel (5333 MHz OC)* Memory Boost: A fully-isolated DDR circuit delivers pure data signals for optimal gaming and overclocking performance. XMP profiles in MSI BIOS are MSI OC LAB optimized and can be easily enabled with auto power settings for optimized memory speed and stability. *1DPC 1R Max. overclocking frequency 5333+ MHz, supports Intel XMP.

DDR4 Memory Boost, PCIe 5.0 x16 Slot, Premium Storage Performance, Wi-Fi 6E Connectivity Fortified PCI-e 5.0 x16 MSI PCI Express Steel Armor slots are secured to the motherboard with extra solder points to support the weight of heavy graphics cards. When every advantage in games counts, Steel Armor also shields the point of contact from electromagnetic interference: 1 x PCI-e 5.0/4.0/3.0 x16 slot* (with Steel Armor**)1 x PCI-e 3.0 x16 slot* *Supports x16/x4 **MSI Surface Mount Technology (SMT) solder welding improves signal clarity. Gen4 M.2 Connectors The MAG B760 TOMAHAWK WIFI DDR4 motherboard features MSI's Gen4 M.2 slots: 3 x Gen4 x4 64Gbps slots* *3 with M.2 Shield Frozr M.2 Shield Frozr Even the world’s fastest SSDs will automatically slow if thermal throttling firmware detects excessively high temperatures. M.2 Shield Frozr is MSI's most advanced thermal solution, offering the best possible protection to ensure maximum SSD transfer speed performance. Wi-Fi 6E & Bluetooth 5.3 2.5G LAN: A Realtek 2.5Gbps LAN controller delivers a premium network gaming experience.Wi-Fi 6E: Features the latest Intel Wi-Fi 6E module (ultra-low latency, high-bandwidth) & Bluetooth 5.3 technology.USB 3.2 Gen 2x2 Type-C: Connect to devices and transfer files at high bandwidth rates: 20Gbps.HD Audio: 7.1-Channel USB High Performance Audio with Audio Boost 5 HD & S/PDIF output.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value, good quality, clean UEFI screen.
reviews.reviewText: Board is pretty sleek looking, has all the M.2 I need, connectors are all there, and I like their UEFI screen so far the best coming from ASUS.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great MB for the price
reviews.reviewText: Keeps temps cool. Up to 7000mhz DDR5. 3 NVMe slots is so much easier. Clean look. Lots of USB ports. Wireless works well when needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars She's a beaut
reviews.reviewText: Got everything set up smoothly and it looks great in my case! This was my first time setting up a PC and I love that it came with directions for both the motherboard and other parts I needed to plug in such as the front panel cables, power connectors, and SATA drives. Make sure you have an Ethernet to set up Windows because you have to install the drivers for wireless use, which I didn't know beforehand.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I used this board for a earlier build this year with a Intel i5-12400 processor. Everything went smoothly except for the DDR5 ram kits. This board or any motherboard may be troublesome enabling XMP memory profile without crashing the PC. I tried 3 sets before I found a set the the motherboard liked. This is true for any DDR5 or motherboard combination as DDR5 is still fairly new.Excellent motherboard though.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Works exactly as advertised. If you pick this up you won't be disappointed!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Cumple con lo que promete, lo unico que podría jugar como punto negativo es que su precio es algo y por el mismo se puede comprar una serie z de la generación pasada (z690)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very easy to install
reviews.reviewText: I just bought this motherboard and it was really easy to install. It came with really clear instructions on how to install everything into it which was really nice. It also powered on on my first try so nothing went wrong.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great motherboard (full black build with a Corsair 4000D) airflow
reviews.reviewText: If your looking to buy a good full ATX mobo, this might be it. It is pricey but it has 7 fan header which very nice, also has 3 m.2 slot which is incredible for expanding storage. It does not have any RGB on the motherboard itself if you care, but it looks great either way.
Excelente para procesadores y tarjetas graficas actuales, un excelente diseño y buena cantidad de puertos M.2 y SATA.

This is a great low-mid motherboard. This fits perfectly in my case corsair D4000 airflow. The built-in I/O was a perfect fit, made for an easy installation. Everything works great out of the box. For a B7 series board, I would rank this as the one to buy because of the features. It has more USB's than most B7 series, as well as Wi-Fi/Bluetooth. Plenty M.2 slots. A great board and a great bargain.
Excelente calidad, conectividad y construcción, yo la uso con un i5-12400f, RTX 4060 y 32GB ram DDR5.Funciona de maravilla y tiene demasiadas características premium para su rango de precio.

Buen diaHace poco compre una tarjeta madre con el fin de actualizar mi set up de hace tiempo, lo primero que llamo la atención es su diseño, lo bien que esta hecho su caja, como acomodan los accesorios, se nota que se toman en serio la presentación del producto, además de estar en vuelta en plástico anti estática. Elegí la B660 TOMAHAWK MSI, debido a que yo tengo GPU de esta marca y ya van 7 años sin tener problemas, por lo que esta claro que su prioridad es la calidad, y durabilidad que es raro en una compañía de tecnología. Me encanta.
